{
  "stem": "27507.10",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "I was even drunk.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "Children were-- there was another child there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was not such a close conspiracy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And to add to that, Koper was member of the underground organization, Polish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the underground organization was a very right wing organization.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they all absolutely hated Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they had-- so they couldn't know anything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they had meetings in one room.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were sitting in the second room.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were listening to the opinions, like it is good that the Jews are now disappeared from Poland, or that Hitler did a good job for us, or something like that, you know?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they were here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he belonged to this right wing organization.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they, of course, were meeting there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were sitting in the next room.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And nobody knew anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was altogether unbelievable--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was all absolutely unbelievable that we survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If the things got really bad, bad, we went into the cellar, which was under the second room.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the cellar, frankly, if you lifted the carpet, you saw the trapdoor to the cellar.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the cellar was only a hiding place in name, but not-- not really-- it was not a proper hiding place.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If somebody would really look for us there, they would find us in 10 minutes at the longest, or less, you know?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we survived there for almost-- well, for a year and a half, almost, for-- because I was there at Koper's from mid-May '43, till mid-September '44, when the Russians finally came and conquered Praga, that part of Warsaw, and liberated us.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was one month-- one year and four months, 16 months, that I didn't leave the flat for one moment.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
